een%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20ask%20for%20my%20husband's%20phone%20or%20social%20media%20passwords%2C%20but%20his%20willingness%20to%20offer%20them%20while%20we%20were%20dating%20has%20made%20me%20feel%20even%20safer%20in%20our%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20Jorge%20and%20I%20went%20to%20high%20school%20together.%20We%20knew%20of%20each%20other%2C%20but%20we%20never%20talked%20to%20each%20other%20or%20spent%20time%20together.%20In%202021%2C%20he%20sent%20me%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-meets-husband-facebook-group-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%20friend%3C%2Fa%3E%20request.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20yeah%2C%20I%20know%20him%2C%20so%20I'll%20accept%20it.%26quot%3B%20After%20we%20connected%20on%20Facebook%20he%20started%20sliding%20into%20my%20DM's%20on%20Instagram%20when%20he%20knew%20I%20was%20single%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20we%20reconnected.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20hanging%20out%20that%20summer%20of%202021%2C%20we%20started%20dating%20and%20were%20inseparable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271ddb9d1-89e4-4841-b7f3-591999b7fec4%5C%22%3EHe%20gave%20me%20his%20passwords%203%20months%20into%20dating%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20three%20months%20into%20dating%2C%20he%20randomly%20texted%20me%20his%20phone%20and%20social%20media%20passwords.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20my%20password%20to%20everything.%20I%20want%20you%20to%20have%20it.%26quot%3B%20I%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20OK.%20I%20don't%20need%20your%20password.%20I%20trust%20you.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20still%20want%20you%20to%20have%20it.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20continued%20dating%20and%20then%20about%20a%20month%20later%2C%20he%20texted%20me%20the%20password%20to%20his%20social%20media%20and%20phone%20again.%20I%20knew%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20communicate%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnever-been-in-a-significant-relationship-marriage-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseriousness%20about%20our%20connection%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20never%20gave%20up%20my%20password%20at%20this%20stage.%20We%20were%20still%20just%20dating%2C%20and%20sharing%20my%20password%20felt%20like%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20more%20serious%2C%20Jorge%20needed%20to%20use%20my%20phone%20for%20something%2C%20and%20since%20he%20didn't%20know%20my%20password%20yet%2C%20I%20shared%20it%20with%20him.%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20password%20I%20use%20for%20everything%20and%20if%20you%20need%20to%20use%20it%2C%20you%20can%20feel%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jorge%20and%20I%20began%20our%20relationship%2C%20we%20both%20had%20boys%20who%20happened%20to%20be%20the%20same%20age%20from%20previous%20relationships%2C%20which%20we%20were%20fine%20with.%20About%20four%20months%20into%20dating%2C%20we%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frefuse-marry-partner-marriage-business-transaction-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalking%20about%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20that's%20when%20I%20had%20to%20be%20clear%20that%20I%20didn't%20want%20any%20more%20kids%2C%20but%20he%20did.%20We%20couldn't%20agree%20on%20whether%20to%20have%20more%20children%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20break%20things%20off%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20short%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpainful-breakup-coworker-forced-work-together-quit-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20about%20two%20weeks%2C%20he%20realized%20he%20was%20OK%20with%20not%20having%20any%20more%20children%20and%20just%20wanted%20to%20be%20with%20me.%20But%20as%20fate%20would%20have%20it%2C%20within%20the%20month%20after%20we%20got%20back%20together%2C%20I%20got%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20married%20in%20January%202022.%20Even%20though%20we%20got%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-young-boyfriend-help-pay-college-tuition-divorce-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarried%20six%20months%20into%20the%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20honesty%20and%20communication%20within%20those%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2256481c91-1aba-464b-be2c-da69261f38ac%5C%22%3EPeople%20on%20the%20internet%20said%20we%20were%20controlling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20shared%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20know%20each%20other's%20phone%20and%20social%20media%20passwords%20on%20TikTok%2C%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20how%20many%20people%20were%20upset.%20People%20argued%20in%20the%20comments%2C%20saying%20we%20were%20controlling%20and%20shouldn't%20be%20together%20if%20we%20can't%20trust%20each%20other.%20But%20we're%20married%20and%20share%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20not%20only%20passwords%20but%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshared-bank-account-benefits-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebank%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20meeting%20my%20husband%2C%20I%20caught%20my%20previous%20partner%20talking%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicro-cheating-behavior-etiquette-dating-tiktok-innocent-guilty-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflirting%20with%20other%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20social%20media.%20A%20year%20into%20our%20marriage%2C%20I%20had%20never%20checked%20his%20phone%20despite%20having%20his%20password%20since%20we%20were%20dating%2C%20but%20one%20night%2C%20I%20woke%20up%20randomly%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20and%20decided%20to%20check%20it.%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20he%20wasn't%20talking%20to%20or%20flirting%20with%20other%20people%20on%20social%20media%20like%20my%20last%20partner.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20through%20every%20social%20media%20account%20and%20his%20messages%20and%20found%20nothing.%20I%20put%20his%20phone%20back%20and%20went%20to%20sleep.%20I%20didn't%20tell%20him%20I%20went%20through%20his%20phone%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20him%20to%20think%20I%20didn't%20trust%20him%2C%20and%20he%20gave%20me%20his%20password%20for%20a%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20finally%20told%20him%20I%20went%20through%20his%20phone%20a%20few%20months%20later.%20He%20was%20OK%20with%20me%20checking%20but%20said%20what%20I%20experienced%20with%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstaying-close-ex-husband-family-divorce-grief-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eex-partner%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20he%20would%20never%20do%20anything%20to%20harm%20our%20family%20or%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20or%20two%20after%20I%20confessed%20to%20checking%20his%20phone%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20I%20felt%20him%20take%20my%20phone%20while%20he%20thought%20I%20was%20sleeping.%20I%20moved%20to%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20I%20was%20waking%20up%2C%20and%20he%20quickly%20put%20my%20phone%20back%20under%20the%20pillow.%20I%20never%20told%20him%20I%20was%20awake%2C%20but%20I%20was%20fine%20he%20went%20through%20my%20phone.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20checked%20his%20phone%20since%20then%2C%20and%20to%20my%20knowledge%2C%20he%20hasn't%20checked%20mine.%20It's%20always%20there.%20I%20have%20access%20to%20it%20but%20don't%20have%20a%20reason%20to%20go%20through%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20never%20had%20a%20partner%20offer%20to%20give%20me%20their%20passwords%2C%20and%20knowing%20my%20husband%20would%20willingly%20give%20me%20access%20without%20asking%20plays%20a%20big%20role%20in%20my%20feeling%20secure%20in%20our%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20an%20interesting%20personal%20story%20about%20your%20marriage%20or%20relationship%3F%20Get%20in%20touch%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acgriffin%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Ecgriffin%40businessins