%20workers%20are%20more%20alert%20and%20inspired%2C%20he%20wrote%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20because%20Cheng%20isn't%20really%20an%20executive.%20He's%20a%2035-year-old%20comedian%20in%20London%20who%20has%20crafted%20a%20satirical%20CEO%20personality%20on%20the%20professional-networking%20platform%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20connect%20with%20you%2C%20emotionally%20%3A)%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20LinkedIn%20tagline%20reads.%20He%20writes%20posts%20in%20what%20has%20become%20classic%2C%20and%20chaotic%2C%20LinkedIn%20style%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpen%20with%20a%20life%20or%20work%20conundrum%20(from%20providing%20difficult%20feedback%20to%20a%20direct%20report%20to%20confessing%20that%20you%20have%20difficulty%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eurinating%20in%20public%20restrooms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20out%20each%20sentence%20or%20clause%20into%20its%20own%20paragraph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20build%20suspense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20wrap%20it%20all%20up%20with%20some%20unexpected%20lesson%20learned%20that%20has%20further%20propelled%20you%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheng's%20wisdom%20includes%20the%20realization%20that%20it's%20OK%20for%20men%20to%20cry%20if%20it's%20over%20the%20end%20of%20tax%20loopholes%2C%20that%20swapping%20raises%20for%20an%20air-hockey%20table%20is%20great%20for%20morale%2C%20and%20that%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20justify%20watching%20porn%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20absurdity%20resonates%20with%20workers%20scrolling%20their%20professional%20feeds%2C%20where%20his%20posts%20often%20blend%20in%20so%20seamlessly%20people%20can't%20tell%20whether%20they're%20satire.%20Cheng%20has%20gained%20thousands%20of%20followers%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20and%20even%20about%207%2C000%20in%20the%20past%20week%20as%20his%20posts%20have%20gone%20viral%20and%20been%20shared%20by%20others%20on%20Reddit%20and%20X.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20has%20met%20a%20boss.%20Everyone%20has%20met%20a%20person%20who%20has%20hit%20the%20top%20end%20and%20they're%20just%20not%20very%20smart%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20told%20me%20of%20his%20craft.%20Collectively%2C%20we're%20watching%20as%20billionaire%20tech%20CEOs%20make%20outlandish%20style%20choices%20and%20challenge%20each%20other%20to%20cage%20matches.%20The%20comedy%20comes%20in%20part%20from%20%26quot%3Bseeing%20these%20insanely%20rich%20people%20lose%20their%20minds%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20LinkedIn%20is%20one%20of%20the%20places%20we're%20all%20watching%20that%20happen%20in%20real%20time.%20But%20can%20a%20platform%20known%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-cringe-how-to-post-new-job-hiring-resume-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecringe%3C%2Fa%3E%20humblebragging%20and%20manufactured%20corporate%20enthusiasm%20become%20actually%20funny%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComedians%20like%20Cheng%20are%20posting%20on%20it%20as%20LinkedIn%20content%20has%20gotten%20far%20weirder.%20It's%20a%20place%20that%20lays%20bare%2C%20as%20my%20colleague%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%3Fsrc%3Dlongreads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERob%20Price%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20it%2C%20how%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20really%20knows%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20'professional'%20anymore.%26quot%3B%20The%20screenshots%20of%20deranged%20posts%20that%20fill%20the%20subreddit%20r%2FLinkedInLunatics%20and%20the%20X%20account%20%40BestofLinkedin%20capture%20the%20vibe%20shift%20of%20the%20once%20buttoned-up%20social%20network.%20There%20are%20bosses%20who%20applaud%20themselves%20as%20innovative%20leaders%20for%20instituting%20company%20policies%20like%20no%20raises.%20There%20are%20oversharers%20divulging%20too%20much%20about%20their%20personal%20lives%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-linkedin-profile-professional-skills-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edivorces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20exotic%20vacations%2C%20and%2C%20in%20at%20least%20one%20instance%2C%20five%20lessons%20on%20principles%20from%20when%20a%20startup%20worker's%20CEO%20slept%20with%20the%20employee's%20wife%20%26quot%3Bin%20retaliation%20for%20my%20pushback%20on%20him%20at%20work.%26quot%3B%20Last%20week%2C%20Ryan%20Salame%2C%20a%20former%20co-CEO%20of%20FTX%2C%20posted%20one%20of%20LinkedIn's%20typical%20new%20job%20updates%2C%20tongue%20in%20cheek%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20happy%20to%20share%20that%20I'm%20starting%20a%20new%20position%20as%20Inmate%20at%20FCI%20Cumberland!%26quot%3B%20(His%20profile%20is%20no%20longer%20available.)%20Salame%20is%20serving%20seven%20years%20in%20prison%20in%20Maryland%20for%20campaign-finance%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20humor%20is%20a%20well-trodden%20trope.%20%26quot%3BOffice%20Space%26quot%3B%20remains%20a%20cult%20classic%20for%20its%20wry%20commentary%20on%20micromanaging%20bosses%2C%20long%20commutes%2C%20and%20the%20catharsis%20of%20exacting%20revenge%20on%20the%20printer%20for%20another%20paper%20jam.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20take%20on%20corporate%20life%20with%20a%20buffoon%20as%20a%20boss%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20both%20cringe-inducing%20and%20redeeming.%20Maybe%20work%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20a%20family%2C%20we're%20nearly%20convinced%20after%20many%20seasons%20of%20watching%20Michael%20Scott%20long%20for%20connection%20and%20the%20blossoming%20of%20workplace%20romances.%20Fittingly%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20most%20streamed%20show%20of%202020.%20Locked%20down%20at%20home%2C%20America%20was%20nostalgic%20for%20a%20more%20winsome%20view%20of%20office%20life.%20Post-pandemic%2C%20workplace%20humor%20has%20taken%20a%20far%20more%20pointed%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20instead%20of%20poking%20fun%20at%20the%20mundanities%20of%20office%20life%20or%20a%20quirky%20boss%2C%20LinkedIn%20comedians%20such%20as%20Cheng%20take%20aim%20at%20their%20CEOs'%20egos%20and%20tone%20deafness.%20They%20question%20company%20loyalty%2C%20the%20grinding%20mindset%2C%20and%20other%20ideals%20that%20have%20long%20been%20the%20mark%20of%20a%20reliable%20worker%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20having%20%26quot%3Ba%20case%20of%20the%20Mondays.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheng%20says%20he%20has%20never%20worked%20a%20corporate%20job%3B%20he's%20always%20been%20a%20comedian%20and%20an%20online%20poker%20player.%20%26quot%3BI've%20always%20been%20against%20corporate%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20respected%20people%20who%20have%20risen%20up%20in%20those%20structures.%26quot%3B%20But%20since%20he%20started%20using%20LinkedIn%20for%20comedy%2C%20he%20sees%20a%20larger%20shift.%20The%20pandemic%20made%20more%20people%20think%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20means%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20We're%20living%20in%20a%20world%20of%20anti-work%20culture%20fueled%20by%20post-peak-pandemic%20changes%20that%20had%20people%20reevaluating%20their%20priorities%20and%20relationship%20to%20work.%20Viral%20posts%20about%20bad%20bosses%20pushed%20an%20anti-work%20sentiment%2C%20previously%20a%20more%20niche%20idea%2C%20into%20the%20mainstream%20in%202021.%20In%20a%202023%20Gallup%20survey%2C%20just%20one-third%20of%20US%20workers%20said%20they%20felt%20engaged%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20compared%20to%2040%25%20in%202020.%20But%20in%20a%202023%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%2C%20just%2011%25%20of%20workers%20said%20they%20felt%20dissatisfied%20with%20their%20boss%20%E2%80%94%20while%2026%25%20said%20they%20felt%20dissatisfied%20with%20their%20pay.%20Books%20like%20%26quot%3BWork%20Won't%20Love%20You%20Back%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Good%20Enough%20Job%2C%26quot%3B%20published%20in%202021%20and%202023%2C%20respectively%2C%20have%20been%20popular.%20Workplace%20trends%20like%20the%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Resignation%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20quitting%26quot%3B%20showcase%20the%20refusal%20to%20work%20under%20exploitative%20conditions%20for%20unfair%20wages%20and%20a%20rejection%20of%20the%20power-hungry%20grind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20corporate%20trolling's%20momentum%20is%20building.%20John%20Mulaney%20roasted%20Salesforce%20workers%20when%20hired%20to%20perform%20at%20the%20company's%20annual%20Dreamforce%20event%20in%20September.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20vaguest%20language%20ever%20devised%20has%20been%20used%20here%20in%20the%20last%20three%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Mulaney%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20there%20are%2045%2C000%20'trailblazers'%20here%20couldn't%20devalue%20the%20title%20any%20more.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20mindset%20that%20finds%20its%20way%20onto%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram's%20Reels%2C%20too%3A%20Comedians%20there%20make%20skits%20about%20their%20day%20jobs%20in%20front%20of%20computers.%20And%20the%20critiques%20increasingly%20take%20on%20topics%20about%20the%20larger%20value%20companies%20and%20work%20have%20in%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20snark%2C%20typically%20found%20on%20X%2C%20has%20seeped%20into%20LinkedIn%2C%20a%20much%20rosier%2C%20earnest%20platform.%20%26quot%3BThe%20environment%20is%20not%20at%20all%20built%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20Roeder%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20humor%20writer%20and%20former%20editor%20at%20The%20Onion%2C%20said%20of%20the%20marriage%20between%20comedy%20and%20LinkedIn.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20just%20kind%20of%20imposed%20themselves%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20one%20of%20those%20people.%20Roeder%20quit%20X%20and%20started%20writing%20joke%20posts%20on%20LinkedIn%20about%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20he%20said%2C%20after%20becoming%20%26quot%3Bdisillusioned%26quot%3B%20with%20what%20X%20has%20become.%20He%20sometimes%20gets%20replies%20from%20people%20trying%20to%20be%20helpful%2C%20not%20understanding%20that%20he's%20satirizing%20the%20platform%20and%20the%20employment%20climate%20itself.%20%26quot%3BI%20almost%20find%20it%20sweet%20when%20I%20post%20something%20nonsensical%2C%20when%20someone%20swoops%20in%20with%20some%20helpful%20advice%20and%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20Roeder%20said.%20That%20sort%20of%20earnestness%20is%20as%20much%20a%20part%20of%20LinkedIn%20as%20the%20inspirational%20bragging.%20LinkedIn%20posts%20can%20expose%20just%20as%20much%20about%20one%20person's%20struggle%20to%20find%20work%20as%20they%20can%20about%20another's%20boasted%20success.%20%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20'Dilbert%2C'%26quot%3B%20Roeder%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20chore%20of%20finding%20work%20in%20this%20economy%20and%20not%20really%20understanding%20what%20this%20economy%20even%20wants%20from%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20own%20relationship%20to%20jokes%20is%20complicated.%20The%20platform%20is%20focused%20on%20promoting%20%26quot%3Bknowledge%26quot%3B%20content%2C%20or%20posts%20that%20offer%20advice%20and%20insights.%20But%20as%20LinkedIn's%20editor%20in%20chief%20Daniel%20Roth%20has%20said%2C%20content%20creators%20have%20a%20balance%20to%20strike%20while%20showcasing%20productivity%3A%20Followers%20%26quot%3Balso%20want%20to%20see%20your%20personality%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20can%20have%20fun%20while%20doing%20both.%20Work%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20homework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnhinged%20LinkedIn%20content%20must%20hit%20a%20sort%20of%20tipping%20point.%20It's%20unlikely%20that%20comedy%20can%20become%20a%20staple%20of%20the%20platform%20in%20the%20way%20that%20%26quot%3Bshitposting%26quot%3B%20thrives%20on%20X%20and%20Reddit%2C%20or%20comedians%20in%20skits%20do%20on%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20LinkedIn%20lends%20itself%20to%20niche%20humor%20on%20office%20and%20remote-work%20culture.%20The%20occasional%20laugh%20to%20break%20up%20a%20feed%20of%20job%20seeking%20and%20brownnosing%20is%20refreshing%2C%20but%20being%20funny%20on%20LinkedIn%20ultimately%20still%20serves%20the%20platform's%20foundational%20purposes%3A%20self-promotion%20and%20networking.%20Cheng%20said%20the%20posts%20had%20helped%20him%20to%20get%20comedy%20gigs%2C%20but%20they've%20also%20unlocked%20new%20work%20on%20the%20platform%20itself%3A%20as%20a%20LinkedIn%20ghostwriter%20for%20executives.%20He's%20trying%20it%20out%2C%20writing%20in%20his%20catchy%20style%20but%20with%20the%20more%20subdued%20musings%20of%20a%20real%20CEO%2C%20he%20said.%20Maybe%20not%20everyone%20gets%20the%20joke.%20But%20some%20see%20the%20following%20he's%20built%2C%20and%20they're%20hungry%20for%20that%20same%20LinkedIn%20clout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-hottest-comedy-club-linkedin-satire-unhinged-ceos-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729158721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670d59d86ac7b701e7cae117%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-hottest-comedy-club-linkedin-satire-unhinged-ceos-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'I've%20been%20watching%20porn%20at%20work%20for%2020%20years.'%20Meet%20the%20standup%20comedians%20satirizing%20your%20boss%20on%20the%20professional%20networking%20platform.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-hottest-comedy-club-linkedin-satire-unhinged-ceos-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22