m%2F2024-10%2Fln1dupdo_pakistan_625x300_17_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20generating%20days%20of%20excitement%20in%20the%20media%2C%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organisation%20(SCO)%20summit%20finally%20concluded%20with%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20making%20a%20quick%20visit%20to%20Islamabad.%20For%20all%20the%20speculation%20about%20India%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20what%20the%2023rd%20meeting%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20Heads%20of%20Government%20(CHG)%20of%20the%20SCO%20will%20likely%20be%20remembered%20for%20is%20perhaps%20Jaishankar's%20sunglasses.%20In%20this%20age%20of%20intense%20social%20media%20scrutiny%2C%20a%20small%20clip%2C%20now%20viral%2C%20of%20Jaishankar%20sporting%20his%20sunglasses%20in%20style%20became%20symbolic%20of%20India's%20confidence%20in%20dealing%20with%20Pakistan.%20Hilarious%20though%20this%20might%20seem%2C%20all%20that%20is%20left%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20Indian%20foreign%20policy%20imagination%20today%20is%20decoding%20our%20diplomats'%20style%20and%20body%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20of%20course%2C%20in%20sending%20Jaishankar%20to%20Islamabad%20for%20the%20SCO%20summit%2C%20New%20Delhi%20was%20also%20sending%20out%20a%20message%20about%20keeping%20its%20engagement%20with%20its%20SCO%20partners%20intact.%20Last%20year%2C%20when%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%20visited%20Goa%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20SCO%20meeting%2C%20he%20became%20the%20first%20Pakistani%20foreign%20minister%20to%20visit%20India%20since%202011.%20And%20now%2C%20Jaishankar%20was%20the%20first%20Indian%20foreign%20minister%20to%20visit%20Pakistan%20in%20around%20a%20decade.%20These%20visits%20though%20were%20largely%20inconsequential%20in%20the%20wider%20scheme%20of%20bilateral%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETerrorism%20Continues%20To%20Upset%20Things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablished%20in%202001%20and%20including%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20India%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Kyrgyzstan%2C%20Tajikistan%2C%20Uzbekistan%2C%20and%20Iran%2C%20the%20SCO%20is%20a%20Eurasian%20grouping%20that%20started%20out%20as%20a%20platform%20to%20deal%20with%20regional%20security%20challenges%20like%20extremism%20and%20terrorism.%20It%20later%20expanded%20to%20facilitating%20trade%20and%20investment%20and%20strengthening%20economic%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20inception%2C%20the%20SCO%20has%20prioritised%20the%20fight%20against%20terrorism%2C%20separatism%2C%20and%20extremism%2C%20as%20stated%20in%20Article%201%20of%20its%20charter.%20India%20has%20focused%20on%20eliminating%20terrorism%20and%20terrorist%20groups%20along%20its%20northwest%20border%20while%20also%20promoting%20connectivity%20and%20socio-economic%20development%20across%20Eurasia.%20However%2C%20despite%20the%20SCO's%20goals%2C%20some%20member%20states%20have%20leveraged%20terrorism%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20exacerbating%20tensions%20in%20Eurasia%20and%20against%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShifting%20geopolitical%20interests%20among%20the%20member%20countries%20have%20hindered%20the%20SCO's%20effectiveness%20in%20tackling%20state-sponsored%20terrorism.%20New%20Delhi%20has%20consistently%20advocated%20for%20greater%20cooperation%20on%20counterterrorism%20and%20has%20raised%20concerns%20about%20state-sponsored%20terrorism%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20Pakistan-based%20groups.%20But%20this%20has%20seen%20limited%20success.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20differing%20views%20on%20achieving%20a%20peaceful%2C%20prosperous%2C%20and%20stable%20Afghanistan%20underscore%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20this%20Eurasian%20organisation%2C%20as%20member%20states%20often%20prioritise%20their%20own%20interests%20over%20a%20collective%20vision%20for%20peace%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'Three%20Evils'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20meeting%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20Jaishankar%20reminded%20the%20SCO%20about%20its%20original%20mandate%20and%20the%20need%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20fundamentals.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20axiomatic%20that%20development%20and%20growth%20require%20peace%20and%20stability.%20And%20as%20the%20Charter%20spelt%20out%2C%20this%20means%20being%20firm%20and%20uncompromising%20in%20countering%20the%20'three%20evils'.%20If%20activities%20across%20borders%20are%20characterised%20by%20terrorism%2C%20extremism%20and%20separatism%2C%20they%20are%20hardly%20likely%20to%20encourage%20trade%2C%20energy%20flows%2C%20connectivity%20and%20people-to-people%20exchanges%20in%20parallel%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20underlined%20for%20the%20gathering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Pakistan%20was%20the%20target%20above%2C%20China%20was%20also%20not%20spared%20when%20he%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3B...Cooperation%20must%20be%20based%20on%20mutual%20respect%20and%20sovereign%20equality%2C%20recognise%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty%20and%20be%20built%20on%20genuine%20partnerships%2C%20not%20unilateral%20agendas.%20SCO%20cannot%20progress%20if%20we%20cherry-pick%20global%20practices%2C%20especially%20of%20trade%20and%20transit.%26quot%3B%20In%20line%20with%20its%20stated%20policy%2C%20India%20refused%20to%20endorse%20China's%20%26quot%3BOne%20Belt%20One%20Road%26quot%3B%20initiative%2C%20thereby%20standing%20out%20in%20the%20SCO%2C%20where%20other%20members%20reaffirmed%20their%20support%20for%20China's%20connectivity%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESCO%20Meet%20Was%20About%20Central%20Asia%2C%20Not%20Pakistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChallenges%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20China%20notwithstanding%2C%20Central%20Asia%20remains%20an%20important%20foreign%20policy%20priority%20for%20India.%20Jaishankar's%20visit%20to%20Islamabad%20was%20a%20testament%20to%20that.%20Since%20becoming%20a%20full%20member%20in%202017%2C%20India%20has%20prioritised%20combating%20terrorism%2C%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20advocate%20for%20stronger%20counterterrorism%20measures%20and%20greater%20cooperation%20among%20member%20states%20to%20address%20this%20pressing%20issue.%20India's%20approach%20also%20focuses%20on%20connectivity%20and%20socio-economic%20development%20across%20Eurasia%2C%20aligning%20with%20its%20broader%20foreign%20policy%20objectives.%20Initiatives%20like%20the%20International%20North-South%20Transport%20Corridor%20and%20the%20Chabahar%20Port%20project%20demonstrate%20New%20Delhi's%20commitment%20to%20enhancing%20trade%20and%20connectivity%20within%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20relationship%20with%20Pakistan%20is%20unlikely%20to%20change%20any%20time%20soon.%20It%20was%20only%20months%20back%20that%20Jaishankar%20had%20declared%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bera%20of%20uninterrupted%20dialogue%26quot%3B%20with%20Pakistan%20was%20over.%20%26quot%3BActions%20have%20consequences%2C%20and%20as%20far%20as%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20concerned%2C%20Article%20370%20is%20done%20%5Baway%20with%5D.%20The%20issue%20now%20is%20what%20kind%20of%20relationship%20we%20can%20contemplate%20with%20Pakistan.%20We%20are%20not%20passive%3B%20whether%20events%20take%20a%20positive%20or%20negative%20direction%2C%20we%20will%20react%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20suggested.%20For%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20there%20is%20neither%20any%20incentive%20nor%20any%20interlocutor%20on%20the%20other%20side%20to%20merit%20a%20change%20in%20its%20approach.%20By%20visiting%20Islamabad%2C%20Jaishankar%20was%20signalling%20to%20the%20SCO%20members%20that%20New%20Delhi%20remains%20committed%20to%20the%20regional%20grouping%20despite%20the%20challenges%20it%20faces%20within.%20Pakistan%20was%20merely%20a%20sideshow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Harsh%20V.%20Pant%20is%20Vice%20President%20%E2%80%93%20Studies%20and%20Foreign%20Policy%2C%20at%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%2C%20and%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20King's%20College%20London.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%