r%20if%20change%20is%20possible%2C%20if%20you%20ever%20wonder%20if%20what's%20broken%20can%20be%20fixed%2C%20if%20you%20ever%20wonder%20whether%20the%20government%20can%20turn%20a%20promise%20broken%20into%20a%20promise%20kept%2C%20just%20look%20at%20what%20President%20Biden%20and%20Vice%20President%20Harris%20did%20for%20these%201%20million%20public%20servants%20across%20the%20country%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20told%20reporters%20on%20a%20Wednesday%20press%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20borrowers%20in%20public%20service%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-debt-cancellation-payment-pause-borrowers-disabilities-defrauded-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20not%20approved%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20relief%20through%20PSLF%20due%20to%20flaws%20within%20the%20program%2C%20including%20rejections%20due%20to%20paperwork%20errors%20and%20processing%20backlogs.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fattorneys-general-biden-extend-pslf-waiver-student-debt-confusion-harm-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20steps%20to%20reform%20the%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20reevaluating%20borrowers'%20accounts%20to%20determine%20if%20payments%20they%20previously%20made%20would%20bring%20them%20to%20the%20threshold%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fixes%20have%20resulted%20in%20incremental%20batches%20of%20relief%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%3B%20in%20July%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20approved%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-pslf-borrowers-getting-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E35%2C000%20in%20PSLF%20for%20%241.2%20billion%20in%20debt%20cancellation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20latest%20relief%20comes%20at%20a%20moment%20of%20uncertainty%20for%20millions%20of%20federal%20borrowers.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20group%20of%20GOP%20state%20attorneys%20general%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-lower-monthly-payments-save-plan-courts-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblock%20Biden's%20new%20SAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20intended%20to%20give%20borrowers%20more%20affordable%20monthly%20payments%20with%20a%20shorter%20timeline%20for%20loan%20forgiveness.%20A%20federal%20court%20blocked%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20plan%20pending%20a%20final%20decision%20on%20its%20legality%2C%20leaving%208%20million%20enrolled%20borrowers%20in%20limbo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Biden's%20second%20attempt%20at%20broader%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-first-lawsuit-broad-debt-cancellation-biden-relief-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20also%20stalled%20in%20court%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20his%20first%20try%20at%20broad%20debt%20relief%20last%20summer%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20announced%20a%20Plan%20B%20that%20would%20forgive%20student%20debt%20for%20borrowers%20under%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20of%201965%2C%20expected%20to%20benefit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-announces-new-student-loan-forgiveness-plan-who-qualifies-relief-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2030%20million%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20department%20has%20not%20yet%20released%20a%20final%20rule%20for%20the%20relief%2C%20a%20federal%20court%20placed%20a%20preliminary%20injunction%20on%20the%20plan%20following%20a%20lawsuit%20from%20GOP%20attorneys%20general%20who%20said%20the%20department%20was%20violating%20administration%20procedure%20by%20planning%20to%20implement%20the%20relief%20ahead%20of%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20administration%20official%20told%20reporters%20on%20the%20Wednesday%20press%20call%20that%20the%20Education%20Department%20will%20continue%20moving%20forward%20with%20targeted%20forms%20of%20debt%20relief%20for%20borrowers%20while%20its%20broader%20plans%20remain%20on%20hold%20as%20the%20legal%20process%20progresses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20day%20one%20of%20my%20Administration%2C%20I%20promised%20to%20fight%20to%20ensure%20higher%20education%20is%20a%20ticket%20to%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20not%20a%20barrier%20to%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said%20in%20a%20Thursday%20statement.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20never%20stop%20working%20to%20make%20higher%20education%20affordable%20%E2%80%93%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20times%20Republican%20elected%20officials%20try%20to%20stop%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-pslf-more-borrowers-approved-debt-cancellation-biden-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729155661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670fce71a70318649282d2fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-pslf-more-borrowers-approved-debt-cancellation-biden-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20announcement%20brings%20the%20total%20number%20of%20borrowers%20approved%20for%20relief%20through%20PSLF%20to%201%20million.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-pslf-more-borrowers-approved-debt-cancellation-biden-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennials%20on%20track%20to%20retire%20early%20are%20maxing%20out%20HSAs%20to%20supplement%20their%20savings.%20Here's%20who%20is%20eligible%20for%20this%20account%20and%20how%20to%20use%20it%20to%20grow%20your%20money.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223085%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22amberly%20grant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67100429a703186492833304%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222314%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmberly%20Grant%2C%2036%2C%20considers%20herself%20'coast%20FIRE.'%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Amberly%20Grant%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFinancially%20savvy%20millennials%20are%20maxing%20out%20HSAs%20to%20supplement%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHSAs%20require%20enrollment%20in%20a%20high-deductible%20health%20plan%2C%20suitable%20for%20healthy%20individuals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%202024%2C%20individuals%20can%20contribute%20up%20to%20%244%2C150%20in%20an%20HSA.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Amberly%20Grant%20started%20making%20enough%20money%20to%20invest%2C%20she%20opened%20and%20maxed%20out%20three%20different%20accounts%3A%20a%20401(k)%2C%20a%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20and%20an%20HSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20two%20are%20common%20retirement-specific%20accounts.%20The%20latter%2C%20a%20health%20savings%20account%2C%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20for%20health%20costs%2C%20but%20financially%20savvy%20individuals%20are%20investing%20the%20funds%20in%20this%20account%20and%20using%20it%20to%20supplement%20their%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%2C%20who%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffire-movement-retire-early-millennial-how-to-increase-income-invest-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epursuing%20early%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20she's%20maxed%20out%20the%20account%20for%20the%20past%20seven%20years.%20The%20IRS%20adjusts%20the%20annual%20contribution%20limit%20each%20year.%20In%202018%2C%20when%20Grant%20started%20using%20an%20HSA%2C%20individuals%20could%20contribute%20up%20to%20%243%2C450%3B%20in%202024%2C%20the%20limit%20is%20%244%2C150.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20she%20likes%20in%20particular%20about%20an%20HSA%20is%20that%20it%20offers%20a%20triple%20tax%20benefit%3A%20You%20can%20contribute%20pretax%20dollars%20(reducing%20your%20taxable%20income)%2C%20your%20contributions%20and%20earnings%20grow%20tax-free%20over%20time%2C%20and%20you%20can%20withdraw%20your%20money%20tax-free%20to%20cover%20qualified%20medical%20expenses%20(including%20things%20like%20copays%2C%20lab%20fees%2C%20and%20vaccines).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20withdraw%20money%20for%20something%20other%20than%20a%20qualified%20medical%20expense%2C%20you'll%20pay%20ordinary%20income%20taxes%20on%20the%20withdrawal%20and%20owe%20a%2020%25%20early%20withdrawal%20penalty%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20if%20you're%20under%2065.%20After%2065%2C%20you%20can%20use%20your%20HSA%20money%20to%20cover%20any%20expense%20without%20incurring%20a%20penalty%2C%20but%20the%20funds%20are%20subject%20to%20income%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrennan%20and%20Erin%20Schlagbaum%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvesting-in-index-funds-couple-built-million-dollar-net-worth-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20off%20more%20than%20%24300%2C000%20worth%20of%20debt%20before%20building%20a%20seven-figure%20net%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20recognize%20the%20benefits%20of%20this%20specific%20account.%20Brennan%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20has%20their%20investments%20spread%20across%20seven%20types%20of%20accounts%20and%20that%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-millionaire-uses-health-savings-account-has-to-build-wealth-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20HSA%20is%20my%20favorite%20by%20far%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c90c146c-f409-4c60-8038-04a6dd9c5cc1%5C%22%3EWho%20is%20eligible%20to%20open%20an%20HSA%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20use%20an%20HSA%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be%20enrolled%20in%20a%20high-deductible%20health%20plan%20(HDHP)%2C%20a%20type%20of%20health%20insurance%20that%20typically%20has%20lower%20monthly%20premiums%20but%20higher%20out-of-pocket%20costs.%20It%20was%20introduced%20in%202001%20(a%20couple%20of%20years%20before%20HSAs%20made%20their%20debut%20in%202003)%20to%20make%20health%20insurance%20more%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20offers%20a%20lower%20premium%20(the%20amount%20you%20pay%20for%20your%20health%20insurance%20every%20month)%2C%20it%20also%20comes%20with%20a%20higher%20deductible%20as%20the%20name%20suggests.%20The%20latter%20is%20what%20you%20pay%20out-of-pocket%20before%20insurance%20kicks%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20that%20reason%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20best%20option%20for%20everyone.%20If%20you%20have%20an%20existing%20health%20issue%20and%20see%20a%20doctor%20frequently%2C%20or%20you're%20preparing%20for%20a%20major%20medical%20expense%20such%20as%20surgery%20or%20having%20kids%2C%20this%20might%20not%20be%20the%20best%20plan%20type%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHDHPs%20are%20typically%20well%20suited%20for%20very%20healthy%20people%20who%20don't%20plan%20on%20seeking%20medical%20care%20frequently%20and%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20the%20deductible%20upfront%20if%20they%20have%20a%20medical%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%2C%20for%20example%2C%20meets%20those%20requirements.%20%26quot%3BI%20decided%20to%20get%20a%20high%20deductible%20health%20plan%20because%20I%20was%20young%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20expect%20my%20medical%20expenses%20to%20be%20too%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22791d3c71-d74c-46f5-ab0a-31a4a95284c9%5C%22%3EThe%20key%20to%20maximizing%20HSA%20gains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20use%20an%20HSA%20to%20build%20wealth%20over%20time%20like%20Grant%20and%20the%20Schlagbaums%20are%20doing%2C%20there%20are%20essentially%20two%20steps%20to%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20invest%20your%20HSA%20funds.%20When%20you%20contribute%20to%20your%20HSA%2C%20it'll%20sit%20in%20a%20cash%20account%20and%20be%20readily%20available%20for%20you%20to%20use%20with%20a%20debit%20card.%20You'll%20have%20to%20move%20your%20money%20from%20your%20HSA%20to%20your%20HSA%20investment%20account.%20Note%20that%20providers%20may%20require%20you%20to%20reach%20a%20certain%20amount%20before%20you%20can%20invest%20(and%20you%20may%20need%20to%20maintain%20that%20cash%20balance).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20investment%20options%20will%20vary%20depending%20on%20your%20provider.%20You'll%20want%20to%20spend%20some%20time%20researching%20what's%20available%20to%20you.%20Grant%20and%20the%20Schlagbaums%20subscribe%20to%20index%20fund%20investing.%20Brent%20Weiss%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20invests%20his%20HSA%20money%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-building-strategy-rich-use-invest-hsa-max-out-plan-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etarget-date%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20getting%20fancy.%20I'm%20not%20trying%20to%20beat%20the%20market.%20It's%20a%20super-simple%20way%20to%20invest%20your%20money%20and%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20it%20every%20day%2C%20week%2C%20month%2C%20or%20quarter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20invested%20your%20money%2C%20avoid%20touching%20it%20and%20let%20it%20grow%20tax-free%20over%20time.%20Say%20you%20opened%20an%20account%20at%20age%2025%20and%20deposited%20%24100%20each%20month%20into%20an%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20fund.%20Assuming%20an%208%25%20return%2C%20by%20the%20time%20you%20hit%2060%2C%20you'd%20have%20over%20%24200%2C000%20in%20that%20account%20alone.%20If%20you%20deposited%20%24345%20a%20month%20(roughly%20the%20max%20you%20can%20contribute%20as%20an%20individual%20in%202024)%2C%20you'd%20end%20up%20with%20over%20%24700%2C000%20by%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20touching%20your%20HSA%20funds%20means%20covering%20your%20medical%20expenses%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20which%20is%20what%20Grant%20and%20the%20Schlagbaums%20do.%20They%20also%20save%20all%20of%20their%20receipts%20from%20health-related%20expenses.%20That%20way%2C%20they%20can%20reimburse%20themselves%20from%20their%20HSA%20at%20any%20time%20if%20they%20need%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Schlagbaums%20save%20every%20health-related%20receipt%20in%20an%20email%20folder%20and%20track%20their%20health-related%20expenses%20in%20an%20Excel%20spreadsheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Excel%20template%20says%20the%20date%2C%20the%20time%2C%20what%20it%20was%20for%2C%20and%20the%20amount%2C%20and%20then%20I%20can%20cross-reference%20to%20my%20email%20folder%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Brennan.%20%26quot%3BSo%20in%20the%20future%2C%20I%20could%20pull%2C%20let's%20call%20it%2C%20%2430%2C000%2C%20theoretically.%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%3B%20I'm%20going%20to%20let%20it%20sit%20there%20and%20invest.%20That's%20the%20whole%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EHave%20you%20used%20an%20HSA%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%3F%20We%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you!%20Email%20kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20to%20share%20your%20story.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-health-savings-account-retirement-tool-investing-wealth-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729155601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671005406ac7b701e7cc8276%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-health-savings-account-retirement-tool-investing-wealth-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20have%20a%20high%20deductible%20health%20plan%20(HDHP)%2C%20you%20can%20save%20and%20invest%20in%20a%20health%20savings%20account%20(HSA).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22h