ship%20under%20this%20will%20retain%20their%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20came%20on%20a%20petition%20that%20contended%20that%20the%20arrival%20of%20Bangladeshi%20refugees%20had%20impacted%20the%20demographic%20balance%20of%20Assam.%20It%20said%20Section%206A%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20violated%20the%20political%20and%20cultural%20rights%20of%20the%20original%20residents%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20the%20enactment%20of%20Section%206A%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20solution%26quot%3B%20to%20a%20unique%20problem%20faced%20by%20Assam%20since%20the%20influx%20of%20refugees%20had%20threatened%20its%20culture%20and%20demography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20central%20government%20could%20have%20extended%20the%20act%20to%20other%20areas%20as%20well%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20do%20so%20because%20it%20was%20unique%20to%20Assam.%20The%20number%20of%20migrants%20coming%20to%20Assam%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20culture%20etc.%20is%20higher%20in%20Assam.%20The%20impact%20of%2040%20lakh%20migrants%20in%20Assam%20is%20more%20than%20that%20of%2057%20lakh%20in%20West%20Bengal%20because%20the%20land%20area%20in%20Assam%20is%20less%20than%20that%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Assam%20Accord%20was%20signed%20on%20August%2015%2C%201985%20between%20the%20centre%20and%20representatives%20of%20the%20Assam%20movement%20in%20response%20to%20a%20massive%20refugee%20influx%20during%20the%20Bangladesh%20liberation%20war.%20As%20a%20humanitarian%20measure%2C%20Section%206A%20was%20added%20to%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20to%20allow%20the%20migrants%20who%20came%20before%20March%2025%2C%201971%20to%20get%20Indian%20citizenship%2C%20but%20without%20voting%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20the%20centre%20was%20right%20in%20its%20contention%20that%20uncontrolled%20immigration%20in%20Assam%20affected%20its%20culture%20and%20that%20it's%20the%20duty%20of%20the%20government%20to%20prevent%20illegal%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHolding%20that%20March%2025%2C%201971%20was%20a%20reasonable%20cut-off%20date%2C%20the%20court%20contended%20that%20Section%206A%20was%20neither%20under-inclusive%20nor%20over-inclusive.%20%26quot%3BCitizenship%20can%20be%20given%20between%20the%20cut-off%20dates%20subject%20to%20fulfilling%20the%20conditions.%20Immigrants%20who%20enter%20after%20March%2025%2C%201971%20cannot%20be%20conferred%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Justice%20Surya%20Kant.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729146180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fef9ofil8_supreme-court-generic_625x300_30_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-upholds-key-section-of-citizenship-act-that-recognises-assam-accord-6808257%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20upheld%20the%20validity%20of%20a%20key%20citizenship%20rule%20that%20recognised%20the%20Assam%20Accord%2C%20granting%20citizenship%20to%20Bangladeshi%20refugees%20who%20had%20arrived%20before%201971.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-upholds-key-section-of-citizenship-act-that-recognises-assam-accord-6808257%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jr%20NTR%E2%80%99s%20Devara%20to%20cross%20Rs%20280%20crore%20mark%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729145861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114305035%2Cimgsize-73856.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftelugu%2Fmovies%2Fbox-office%2Fjr-ntrs-devara-to-cross-rs-280-crore-mark-on-thursday%2Farticleshow%2F114305093.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.india